FBIS4-8931 "dreeu076_i_94031" FBIS-EEU-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Allow Resumption of Medical Aid Serbs Allow Resumption of Medical Aid LD1904134194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1248 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904134194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Belgrade, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- The cabinet of Nikola Koljevic, vice president of the republic of Sprska, today informed the aid organization Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) that the republic of Srpska authorities have authorized this organization, too, to carry on with its humanitarian convoy operations. It was announced yesterday that, under an agreement between the Serbian authorities and Yasushi Akashi, the UN secretary general's special envoy, the UNHCR, the International Committee of the Red Cross, and Handicap International can resume their humanitarian convoy operations. In the TANJUG report, Medecin Sans Frontieres was left out by mistake.
